node.text:
This lighthouse is transformed into a spectacular icicle masterpiece after being frozen by a glacial storm on Lake Michigan in the US.

This incredible photo reflect just how freezing the temperatures can get and it really looks like something out of a wonderful icy fairytale. These ice sculptures accidentally got formed when the lighthouse got hit by splashing waves and a frigid wintry storm, crystallizing the water in place. The storm was so intense that it uplifted the anchors of the scaffolding which had been left there after painting and somehow the cascading icicles make it appear like a stairway, which renders the scene even more magical. 
-----------------------------------‐------------
Photographer: Thomas Zakowski

Mummy Juanita: The Sacrifice of The Inca Ice Maiden

About 600 years ago a 12-15-year-old Inca girl was led up a mountain in Peru. She and the priests at her side had spent a year in preparation for this event. For the girl now called Mummy Juanita, that trek was her last.

The largest known flying creature "Quetzalcoatlus"

Quetzalcoatlus is a pterosaur that lived 65 to 70 million years ago during the late Cretaceous period. It was first discovered in the 1971's and described by Douglas A. Lawson in 1975. It is named after the legendary serpent god Quetzalcoatl.
